            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "An SEZ unit works in a duty free enclave, procures inputs without GST against a letter of undertaking and treats sales into India as imports, while a DTA unit pays GST on inputs and takes credit. An SEZ unit must also stay a net foreign exchange earner over five years and reports performance to the Development Commissioner."
